He only ever took psilocybin once and was so traumatised by the experience that he had to be sedated for 24 hours – this was after he was found wandering about New York’s LaGuardia airport in a distressed state, minus shirt, shoes or socks. As for other inebriating agents, he hasn’t had a drink for over a month, he says proudly. “Nothing but prune juice.” Nor, he reckons, does he have a dark and troubled personality. “Am I moody?” he calls out to his great-niece who is doing some cataloguing for him. “Am I unpredictable?”
